"title": "5330: guard",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5330: guard",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A watchman, sentinel or bodyguard for a king or ruler. The word is also used metaphorically.</p>\n<h2>Bodyguards for kings</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:14\">1SA 22:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam26:14-1Sam26:15\">1SA 26:14–26:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:2\">1SA 28:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam16:6\">2SA 16:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:23\">2SA 23:23</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:25\">1CH 11:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:8\">1KI 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:10\">1KI 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs11:7-2Kgs11:8\">2KI 11:7–11:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr12:11\">2CH 12:11</a></p>\n<h2>Guards at the tomb of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:65-Matt27:66\">MAT 27:65–27:66</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:4\">MAT 28:4</a></p>\n<h2>Other examples of human guards</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:9\">NEH 4:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh4:23\">NEH 4:23</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:4\">LUK 22:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen37:36\">GEN 37:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs25:11\">2KI 25:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer39:9\">JER 39:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:12\">JER 51:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:54\">MAT 27:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:8\">LUK 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:21\">LUK 11:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:52\">LUK 22:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:63\">LUK 22:63</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:1\">ACT 4:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:4\">ACT 12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:6\">ACT 12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:10\">ACT 12:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts12:19\">ACT 12:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:23\">ACT 16:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts22:20\">ACT 22:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:35\">ACT 23:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts24:23\">ACT 24:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:16\">ACT 28:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:13\">PHP 1:13</a></p>\n<h2>Angelic guards</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps91:11-Ps91:12\">PSA 91:11–91:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:24\">GEN 3:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor4:15\">1CO 4:15</a></p>\n<h2>The LORD guards his people himself</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:9-Deut32:11\">DEU 32:9–32:11</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps97:10\">PSA 97:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:15\">GEN 28:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:9\">1SA 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:31\">2SA 22:31</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:30\">PSA 18:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:6\">PSA 1:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps121:3-Ps121:8\">PSA 121:3–121:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:7-Prov2:8\">PRO 2:7–2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov30:5\">PRO 30:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa27:3\">ISA 27:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:5\">ISA 31:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:12\">ISA 52:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa58:8\">ISA 58:8</a></p>\n<h2>Figurative references to guarding</h2>\n<h3>Guarding one's conduct</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:23\">PRO 4:23</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim4:16\">1TI 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:9\">DEU 4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov7:2\">PRO 7:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:17\">PRO 16:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov19:16\">PRO 19:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl5:1\">ECC 5:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:15-Mal2:16\">MAL 2:15–2:16</a>MAT <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal16:6\">16:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:11-Matt16:12\">MAT 16:11–16:12</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:13\">1CO 16:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:7\">PHP 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:17\">2PE 3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2John1:8\">2JN 1:8</a></p>\n<h3>Guarding one's tongue</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps141:3\">PSA 141:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov13:3\">PRO 13:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas3:3-Jas3:8\">JAS 3:3–3:8</a></p>\n<h2>Christians are to guard the gospel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:14\">2TI 1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:30-Acts20:31\">ACT 20:30–20:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:20\">1TI 6:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:14-2Tim4:15\">2TI 4:14–4:15</a></p>\n<h2>Church leaders are to guard those in their care</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28-Acts20:31\">ACT 20:28–20:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:17\">HEB 13:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2\">1PE 5:2</a></p>",
